    {
     "name": "stdout",

     "text": [
      "\n",
      "üìä Summary:\n",
      "Total reviews: 1214\n",
      "Amharic reviews (lang='am'): 0\n",
      "English reviews (lang='en'): 1193\n",
      "English with Amharic meaning (transliterated): 0\n",
      "\n",
      "‚úÖ Classified data saved to 'language_classified_reviews.csv'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: Detect language for each review\n",
    "def detect_language(text):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        return detect(text)\n",
    "    except LangDetectException:\n",
    "        return \"unknown\"\n",
    "\n",
    "df['review'] = df['review'].astype(str)  # Ensure text format\n",
    "df['lang_detected'] = df['review'].apply(detect_language)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: Flag transliterated Amharic written in Latin script\n",
    "def is_transliterated_amharic(text):\n",
    "    # Common Amharic words written in English letters\n",
    "    patterns = ['selam', 'dehna', 'endemin', 'eny', 'betam', 'wedaj', 'tiru', 'yene', 'amasegnallo']\n",
    "    return any(re.search(rf\"\\b{p}\\b\", text.lower()) for p in patterns)\n",
    "\n",
    "df['is_transliterated_amharic'] = df['review'].apply(is_transliterated_amharic)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 4: Count and display statistics\n",
    "total_reviews = len(df)\n",
    "amharic_reviews = df['lang_detected'].value_counts().get('am', 0)\n",
    "english_reviews = df['lang_detected'].value_counts().get('en', 0)\n",
    "translit_amharic_reviews = df['is_transliterated_amharic'].sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nüìä Summary:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total reviews: {total_reviews}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Amharic reviews (lang='am'): {amharic_reviews}\")\n",
    "print(f\"English reviews (lang='en'): {english_reviews}\")\n",
    "print(f\"English with Amharic meaning (transliterated): {translit_amharic_reviews}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 5 (Optional): Save new DataFrame with language classification\n",
    "df.to_csv(\"../data1/language_classified_reviews.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "print(\"\\n‚úÖ Classified data saved to 'language_classified_reviews.csv'\")"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import emoji\n",
    "import spacy\n",
    "from transformers import pipeline\n",
    "from textblob import TextBlob\n",
    "from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer\n",
    "import nltk"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "65d77b0a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[nltk_data] Downloading package vader_lexicon to\n",
      "[nltk_data]     C:\\Users\\ayish\\AppData\\Roaming\\nltk_data...\n",
      "Device set to use cpu\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "üîπ Average Sentiment Score by Bank:\n",
      "        bank  sentiment_score\n",
      "0  Absiniya         0.974693\n",
      "1       Cbe         0.976225\n",
      "2    Dashin         0.962939\n",
      "\n",
      "üîπ Average Sentiment Score by Rating:\n",
      "    rating  sentiment_score\n",
      "0       1         0.984706\n",
      "1       2         0.969573\n",
      "2       3         0.973211\n",
      "3       4         0.952492\n",
      "4       5         0.967090\n",
      "\n",
      "‚úÖ Sentiment results saved to 'bank_reviews_with_sentiment.csv'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Download required NLTK data\n",
    "nltk.download('vader_lexicon')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load NLP tools\n",
    "nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n",
    "vader = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()\n",
    "sent_pipeline = pipeline(\"sentiment-analysis\", model=\"distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 1: Load your data\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(\"../data1/cleaned_reviews.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: Define text cleaning function\n",
    "def clean_text(text):\n",
    "    text = str(text)\n",
    "    text = emoji.replace_emoji(text, replace='')  # Remove emojis\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z\\s]', '', text)       # Remove special characters and numbers\n",
    "    text = text.lower()                           # Lowercase\n",
    "    doc = nlp(text)\n",
    "    tokens = [token.lemma_ for token in doc if not token.is_stop]\n",
    "    return \" \".join(tokens)\n",
    "\n",
    "df['cleaned_review'] = df['review'].apply(clean_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: Run sentiment analysis (Transformers)\n",
    "labels = []\n",
    "scores = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for review in df['cleaned_review']:\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        output = sent_pipeline(review[:512])[0]  # DistilBERT has token limits\n",
    "        labels.append(output['label'])\n",
    "        scores.append(output['score'])\n",
    "    except Exception:\n",
    "        labels.append(\"NEUTRAL\")\n",
    "        scores.append(0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "df['sentiment_label'] = labels\n",
    "df['sentiment_score'] = scores\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 4: (Optional) Add VADER/TextBlob scores\n",
    "df['vader_score'] = df['cleaned_review'].apply(lambda x: vader.polarity_scores(x)['compound'])\n",
    "df['textblob_score'] = df['cleaned_review'].apply(lambda x: TextBlob(x).sentiment.polarity)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 5: Aggregation\n",
    "\n",
    "# 5.1 Sentiment by Bank\n",
    "bank_sentiment = df.groupby('bank')['sentiment_score'].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "print(\"\\nüîπ Average Sentiment Score by Bank:\\n\", bank_sentiment)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 5.2 Sentiment by Rating\n",
    "rating_sentiment = df.groupby('rating')['sentiment_score'].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "print(\"\\nüîπ Average Sentiment Score by Rating:\\n\", rating_sentiment)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 6: Save results\n",
    "df.to_csv(\"../data1/bank_reviews_with_sentiment.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "print(\"\\n‚úÖ Sentiment results saved to 'bank_reviews_with_sentiment.csv'\")"
   ]
  },

    "nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n",
    " #Preprocess Reviews for TF-IDF#\n",
    "def preprocess(text):\n",
    "    doc = nlp(str(text).lower())\n",
    "    tokens = [token.lemma_ for token in doc if token.is_alpha and not token.is_stop]\n",
    "    return \" \".join(tokens)\n",
    "\n",
    "df['tokens'] = df['cleaned_review'].apply(preprocess)"
   ]
  },

   ],
   "source": [
    "#TF-IDF\n",
    "vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=1000, ngram_range=(1, 2))\n",
    "X = vectorizer.fit_transform(df['tokens'])\n",
    "tfidf_df = pd.DataFrame(X.toarray(), columns=vectorizer.get_feature_names_out())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show top keywords per bank\n",
    "keywords_per_bank = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for bank in df['bank'].unique():\n",
    "    subset = df[df['bank'] == bank]\n",
    "    X_sub = vectorizer.transform(subset['tokens'])\n",
    "    avg_scores = X_sub.mean(axis=0)\n",
    "    scores_dict = dict(zip(vectorizer.get_feature_names_out(), avg_scores.A1))\n",
    "    sorted_keywords = sorted(scores_dict.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:20]\n",
    "    keywords_per_bank[bank] = sorted_keywords\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print top 10 keywords for each bank\n",
    "for bank, keywords in keywords_per_bank.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nüîπ Top keywords for {bank}:\")\n",
    "    for word, score in keywords[:10]:\n",
    "        print(f\"{word} ({score:.3f})\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "06c530be",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Manual Clustering into Themes\n",
    "themes = {\n",
    "    \"Account Access Issues\": [\"login\", \"password\", \"account\", \"register\", \"reset\"],\n",
    "    \"Transaction Performance\": [\"transfer\", \"transaction\", \"delay\", \"load\", \"balance\"],\n",
    "    \"User Interface & Experience\": [\"app\", \"interface\", \"slow\", \"crash\", \"design\"],\n",
    "    \"Customer Support\": [\"support\", \"help\", \"response\", \"call\", \"agent\"],\n",
    "    \"Feature Requests\": [\"feature\", \"add\", \"option\", \"statement\", \"notification\"],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "def assign_theme(text):\n",
    "    found_themes = []\n",
    "    for theme, keywords in themes.items():\n",
    "        if any(word in text for word in keywords):\n",
    "            found_themes.append(theme)\n",
    "    return \", \".join(found_themes) if found_themes else \"Other\"\n",
    "\n",
    "df['themes'] = df['tokens'].apply(assign_theme)\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Prepare grouped data\n",
    "theme_counts = df.groupby(['themes', 'bank']).size().reset_index(name='count')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set plot size\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a horizontal bar plot (themes on Y-axis)\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=theme_counts, y='themes', x='count', hue='bank', orient='h')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add titles and labels\n",
    "plt.title(\"Themes Mentioned per Bank\")\n",

    "plt.legend(title='Bank')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show plot\n",
    "plt.show()"

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming your dataframe is named df and has columns: 'bank', 'themes'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Group data\n",
    "theme_counts = df.groupby(['bank', 'themes']).size().reset_index(name='count')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get unique banks\n",
    "banks = theme_counts['bank'].unique()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Styling\n",
    "sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for bank in banks:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nüìä Theme Counts for {bank}:\\n\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Filter data for this bank\n",
    "    bank_data = theme_counts[theme_counts['bank'] == bank].sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Print the counts as a table\n",
    "    print(bank_data[['themes', 'count']].to_string(index=False))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Plot\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "    sns.barplot(data=bank_data, y='themes', x='count', palette='viridis')\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Theme Distribution - {bank}\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Number of Mentions\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Themes\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Sample structure: df with 'bank' and 'themes' columns\n",
    "# Group data\n",
    "theme_counts = df.groupby(['bank', 'themes']).size().reset_index(name='count')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Unique banks\n",
    "banks = theme_counts['bank'].unique()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set Seaborn style\n",
    "sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for bank in banks:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nüìä Theme Counts for {bank}:\\n\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Filter for specific bank\n",
    "    bank_data = theme_counts[theme_counts['bank'] == bank].sort_values(by='count', ascending=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Print counts\n",
    "    print(bank_data[['themes', 'count']].to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 5))\n",
    "    ax = sns.barplot(data=bank_data, x='count', y='themes', palette='viridis')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add labels to bars\n",
    "    for container in ax.containers:\n",
    "        ax.bar_label(container, fmt='%d', label_type='edge', padding=3)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Titles and labels\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Theme Distribution - {bank}\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Number of Mentions\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Themes\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "#WordClouds by Bank\n",
    "from wordcloud import WordCloud\n",
    "\n",
    "for bank in df['bank'].unique():\n",
    "    text = \" \".join(df[df['bank'] == bank]['tokens'])\n",
    "    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(text)\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')\n",
    "    plt.axis(\"off\")\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Top Keywords in Reviews - {bank}\")\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  }
